article.headline: IUPUI 68, Valparaiso 54
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Austin Montgomery and Gary Patterson each scored 15 points to lead IUPUI to a 68-54 win over Valparaiso Thursday night. Angelo Smith added 14 points and Craig Swoope came off the bench to score 11 points for the Jaguars (11-12, 4-5 Mid-Continent Conference). Brandon McPherson scored 15 points and had five rebounds to lead the Crusaders (13-12, 6-4), who were outrebounded 32-19. Jake Diebler added 12 points for Valparaiso. IUPUI shot 8-of-26 (30 percent) from the floor in the first half and trailed 31-25 at halftime. A 3-pointer by Swoope capped an 11-2 second-half run for the Jaguars and gave IUPUI a 13-point lead with 4:09 remaining.
